HEADWORD: Drogher
<hw>Dro"gher</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Drag</er>.]</ety> <def>A small craft used in the West India Islands
to take off sugars, rum, etc., to the merchantmen; also, a vessel for
transporting lumber, cotton, etc., coastwise; <as>as, a lumber
<ex>drogher</ex></as>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>droger</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Ham. Nar. Encyc.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

